You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. Critical

Noto Sans Arabic Cond Light Regular (NotoSansArabic-CondensedLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Arabic Condensed Light' ≠ 'Noto Sans Arabic Cond Light' (NID 1).

Pass

Noto Sans Arabic Cond Regular (NotoSansArabic-Condensed.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansArabic-Condensed', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Sans Arabic Cond Bold (NotoSansArabic-CondensedBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansArabic-CondensedBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Sans Arabic Cond Bold (NotoSansArabic-CondensedBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Arabic Condensed Bold' ≠ 'Noto Sans Arabic Cond Bold' (NID 1 + 'Space' + NID 2).

Pass

Noto Sans Arabic Cond Blk Regular (NotoSansArabic-CondensedBlack.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansArabic-CondensedBlack', Everything looks good.

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Arabic Condensed Black' ≠ 'Noto Sans Arabic Cond Blk' (NID 1).
